      <abstract>
        <p>Sri Lanka's Pres Chandrika Kumaratunga postpones referendum on new Constitution until October 18; ballot measure, scheduled for August 21, has been criticized by opponents and legal experts as vaguely worded and unlawful; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>President Chandrika Kumaratunga has postponed a referendum on a new Constitution until Oct. 18. The ballot measure, which had been scheduled for Aug. 21, had been criticized by opponents and legal experts as vaguely worded and unlawful. The president made no mention of restoring Parliament, which she suspended last month.</p>
        <p>Barry Bearak (NYT)</p>
      </block>
